Description: snapshot backup over SSH/rsync and rclone (CLI + GTK desktop app)
 Moraine creates timestamped, hard-linked snapshots: each backup run looks like
 a complete tree, but unchanged files share disk via hard links, so history
 costs almost nothing. It restores individual files or whole trees, prunes old
 snapshots with a GFS retention policy, and keeps a run log.
 .
 Backends: rsync over SSH, and rclone (cloud, SFTP, SMB, WebDAV, S3, ...).
 .
 This package provides both the command-line client (moraine) and the GTK 4
 desktop application (moraine-gui) — run whichever you prefer.
